external_knowledge:
; "top 5 earners" refers to individuals with the highest wages in each job title and geographic location; 
; The ranking is based on the logarithm of the individual's wage (`log_wage`); 
; The query considers the job title and geographic location as the primary criteria for determining the "field" and "region".

- 'middle-aged' refers to those over 30 years old; 
'seasoned' refers to those with more than 5 years of potential experience; 
'higher-than-average wage' refers to an average log wage value greater than 5.0, which implies a wage greater than exp(5.0).

sql:
SELECT AVG(log_wage) AS average_log_wage
FROM individuals
WHERE employment_status = 'employed' AND potential_experience > 5;
